src:{"type":"field","size":[329,165],"pos":[2,174],"pattern":46,"border":0,"style":"plain","value":"t: select mv:range 9 from nil\nt.xs: 1 + floor  0.5 * t.mv\nt.os:  t.xs - (1-2%t.mv) \nt.sq: t.xs+t.os # squares used should be 1 + mv\n# now, count the possible values:\n# (how many ways to choose sq out of 9) * (how many ways to split xs/os)\nt.pv: each i in range 9 nck[9 t.sq[i]]*nck[t.sq[i] t.xs[i]] end\ng.value: t\n\n# apparently there are 5478 reachable positions\n# so this is pretty good compression\n6045 ~ sum t.pv "}
